Precious.GumedePHOTO: supplied Receiving the second prize for the infection control poster (from left) Jayshree Tanjivelu, Heather Roetz and Dr Miljeko Panajatovic (acting medical manager). Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories AS part of Global Handwashing Day, celebrated on 15 October, Port Shepstone Regional Hospital held a hand hygiene and awards day last Thursday, awarding departments that are doing well in curbing transmission of infections.Hospital spokesperson Phumza Morai said departments were motivated by the activity and educated patients and hospital visitors on hand hygiene practices. On the day, the nursery unit won a floating trophy for the best practice in hand hygiene, G Ward received an award for best wound care practises. The pharmacy won first prize for an infection control poster competition and the supply chain department came second in the same category, said Morai. - Supplied.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.